The Nigeria Airforce on Sunday went on offensive against bandits, destroying logistics stores at a location in Kagara Forest, killing Four armed bandits in the air raid.
The Air Task force carried out the air raid to reinforce Operation DIRAN MIKIYA on receiving reliable intelligence reports which indicated that some of the armed bandits had relocated some logistics items, including fuel, motorcycles and local arms making equipment, to another location
The Airforce said it dispatched an Mi-35 helicopter gunship, and engaged the target, adding that successful hits were recorded on the logistics facility, and it was engulfed in flames.
The north west had been a theatre of violent crimes which have been giving the federal government sleepless nights

			
